element.name: Glencree Cache by Donnacha, Traditional Cache (2/1.5)
element.long-description:
The cache is located in Glencree, Co. Wicklow. Terrain is good, but be careful if it is wet. If there are children with you, keep them close, as there is a river right beside the cache location. The cache is covered by two stones, please replace stones as you found them, or else the cache will be easly seen. Glencree is about 6 miles past Enniskerry Village. The best place to leave your car is at N53 12.043 W6 17.532. (War Graveyard, have a look when your're done caching) From here the cache is a 5 minute walk. Start walking back down the road you just came up. The path starts at a telephone pole, and at this pole you can look down and see a grotto.
Visit the Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE
element.encoded-hints: The cache is hidden under and old tree trunk opposite the grotto and is covered by two stones. Check photo's.

2010-05-12T19:00:00Z : Found it by B&B04
What a beautiful glen and an interesting german soldier graveyard. Many thanks for showing us this place. We searched without the spoiler and found a big container without logbook so we thought at first the cache was muggled. Luckily we looked a second time and found the cache.
Thanks for the cache.
In/out: coin
